        Leafwhisper says, "Three days is standard for Territory One crossing! You've done wonderfully, excellent travel companion really, and the next guides will take excellent care of you—"

        I say, "I know. Just..."
        I look at Rootwalker checking the shelter, at Leafwhisper's shimmering leaves, at Scout bouncing contentedly.
        "Getting used to this team."

        Leafwhisper says, "We'll miss you too—First human traveler! Very memorable experience."

        Rootwalker confirms, "Good traveler."

        High praise, in one word.

        I eat my mushroom paste and try not to think about saying goodbye tomorrow.

        ¶

        But tomorrow will come anyway.

        Tonight, I have this team — this rhythm — this strange found family of chatty leaves and silent roots and a bouncing sphere.

        It is enough — it has to be.
      </text>
